<div id="fb_body_wrapper">
<div id="fb_tab">
<div id="fb_tab_l">Log</div>
<div id="fb_tab_r">&nbsp;<img src="images/fblogo_mini.gif" /></div> 
</div> 
<div id="fb_pg_wrapper">
<div id="fb_pg_body">
	Retourne le logarithme naturel d'un nombre donn&eacute;<br \>
<br \>
<div class="fb_sect_title">Syntaxe</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><tt><br \>
<a href="KeyPgDeclare.html">Declare</a> <a href="KeyPgFunction.html">Function</a> <b>Log</b> <a href="KeyPgCdecl.html">cdecl</a> ( <a href="KeyPgByval.html">ByVal</a> <i>number</i> <a href="KeyPgAs.html">As</a> <a href="KeyPgDouble.html">Double</a> ) <a href="KeyPgAs.html">As</a> <a href="KeyPgDouble.html">Double</a><br \>
</tt><br \>
</div><div class="fb_sect_title">Usage</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><tt><br \>
<i>result</i> = <b>Log</b>( <i>number</i> )<br \>
</tt><br \>
</div><div class="fb_sect_title">Param&egrave;tres</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><br \>
<tt><i>number</i></tt><br \>
<div class="fb_indent">Le nombre pour lequel on calcule le logarithme naturel.<br \>
<br \>
</div></div><div class="fb_sect_title">Valeur retourn&eacute;e</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><br \>
Retourne le logarithme avec la base <i><b>e</b></i> (connu aussi sous le nom de logarithme naturel) de <tt><i>number</i></tt>.<br \>
<br \>
</div><div class="fb_sect_title">Description</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><br \>
Il peut y avoir une certaine confusion avec cette notation &eacute;tant donn&eacute; que dans les math&eacute;matiques la fonction logarithme naturel est g&eacute;n&eacute;ralement not&eacute;e <b>LN</b>, tandis que le logarithme de base 10 est souvent not&eacute;e comme LOG. FreeBasic, comme la plupart des langages de programmation informatique, utilise LOG pour d&eacute;signer le logarithme naturel.  Si <tt><i>number</i></tt> est &eacute;gal &agrave; z&eacute;ro, FreeBasic retourne une valeur sp&eacute;ciale qui repr&eacute;sente "-infinity", affich&eacute; "-Inf".  Si <tt><i>number</i></tt> est inf&eacute;rieur &agrave; z&eacute;ro, <b>Log</b> retourne une valeur sp&eacute;ciale repr&eacute;sentant "non d&eacute;fini", affich&eacute;e "NaN" ou "IND", le texte exact d&eacute;pend de la plate-forme de travail. Si <tt><i>number</i></tt> est une variable non initialis&eacute;e, "-infinity" est retourn&eacute;.<br \>
<br \>
</div><div class="fb_sect_title">Exemple</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><br \>
<tt><div class="freebasic">
<span class="com">'Find&nbsp;the&nbsp;logarithm&nbsp;of&nbsp;any&nbsp;base</span><br />
<span class="key">Function</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">LogBaseX</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">(</span><span class="key">ByVal</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">Number</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">As</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">Double</span><span class="oth">,</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">ByVal</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">BaseX</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">As</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">Double</span><span class="oth">)</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">As</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">Double</span><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="wrd">LogBaseX</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">=</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">Log</span><span class="oth">(</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">Number</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">)</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">/</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">Log</span><span class="oth">(</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">BaseX</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">)</span><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="com">'For&nbsp;reference:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1/log(10)=0.43429448</span><br />
<span class="key">End</span>&nbsp;<span class="key">Function</span><br />
<br />
<span class="key">Print</span>&nbsp;<span class="quo">"The&nbsp;log&nbsp;base&nbsp;10&nbsp;of&nbsp;20&nbsp;is:"</span><span class="oth">;</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">LogBaseX</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">(</span>&nbsp;<span class="num">20</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">,</span>&nbsp;<span class="num">10</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">)</span><br />
<span class="key">Print</span>&nbsp;<span class="quo">"The&nbsp;log&nbsp;base&nbsp;2&nbsp;of&nbsp;16&nbsp;is:"</span><span class="oth">;</span>&nbsp;<span class="wrd">LogBaseX</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">(</span>&nbsp;<span class="num">16</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">,</span>&nbsp;<span class="num">2</span>&nbsp;<span class="oth">)</span><br />
<br />
<span class="key">Sleep</span><br />
</div></tt><br />
<br \>
Affichera:<br \>
<pre class="fb_pre">
The log base 10 of 20 is: 1.301029995663981
The log base 2 of 16 is: 4
</pre><br \>
</ul></div><div class="fb_sect_title">Diff&eacute;rences avec QB</div><div class="fb_sect_cont"><br \>
<ul><li> Aucune<br \>
<br \>
